summary:
Decides to review the implementation of measures in 18 months and make adjustments as necessary; 

 Remains actively seized of the matter.

The Monitoring Team, under the Committee's direction, shall:

* Submit two comprehensive reports (by 30 September 2013 and 30 April 2014) on implementation of measures;
* Assist in reviewing names on the List and developing the Committee's record;
* Follow up on requests to Member States for information;
* Submit a programme of work and detail activities;
* Gather information on non-compliance and submit case studies;
* Provide recommendations to assist Member States;
* Assist in considering proposals for listing and delisting;
* Consult with Member States and encourage submissions for the List;
* Present additional identifying information to keep the List updated.
To collate, assess, monitor and report on implementation of measures; 
pursue case studies; and explore relevant issues as directed by the Committee. 
Consult with Member States, organizations, and bodies, including UNAMA. 
Consult with intelligence and security services to facilitate information sharing. 
Consult with private sector representatives to strengthen assets freeze. 
Work with international organizations to promote awareness and compliance. 
Work with INTERPOL to obtain photographs of listed individuals. 
Assist other subsidiary bodies and expert panels. 
Assist Committee in facilitating capacity-building assistance. 
Report to Committee regularly or upon request. 
Report on linkages between Al-Qaida and eligible individuals/groups. 
Gather information on travel exemptions and report to Committee. 
Undertake other responsibilities identified by the Committee.
